startRecording.title: Start traffic recording
startRecording.info: This will start recording process in background which will be active until you stop it manually or is stopped automatically by defined limits. Note that there can be only one recording active at the same time.
startRecording.infoForFileExport: Once the recording process is finished, a file will be created and be ready for download.

samplingRate.label: Sampling rate
samplingRate.hint: The sampling rate of the traffic recording (100 % means all records will be recorded, 1 % means 1 % of records will be recorded).

validations.notNumber: Sampling rate must be integer number.
validations.outOfRange: Sampling rate must be number between 1 and 100 (inclusive).

maxDurationInMilliseconds.label: Maximum duration
maxDurationInMilliseconds.hint: The duration of the recording, after this time the recording will be stopped automatically. Use combination of h, min, s, or ms units.

validations.notDuration: Maximum duration must be duration string.
validations.outOfRange: Maximum duration must be positive number and less than 2^63-1 in milliseconds.

exportFile.label: Export to file
exportFile.hint: Whether to export the traffic into a file for download once the recording is finished.

hint.default: The size of the recording in bytes, after this size the recording will be stopped automatically. You can use k, M, G, Ki, Mi, or Gi unit prefix.
hint.rounded: The size of the recording will be rounded to full bytes.

validations.notByteSize: Maximum file size must be byte size.
validations.outOfRange: Maximum file size must be positive number and less than 2^63-1.

hint.default: The size of the chunk file in bytes. Individual files in the export file will be approximately this size. You can use k, M, G, Ki, Mi, or Gi unit prefix.
hint.rounded: The size of the chunk file will be rounded to full bytes.

validations.notByteSize: Chunk file size must be byte size.
validations.outOfRange: Chunk file size must be positive number and less than 2^63-1.
